<div class="xl-row xl-middle xl-vjustify">
	<div class="fill-1 col middle justify shaded">
		<div class="col content gap-4">
			<div class="col justify vjustify gap-3">
				<h3>The Schedule</h3>
				<p><strong>On Friday April 8th:</strong> Check-in will start at <strong>6:30pm</strong>, and we'll host the opening ceremony at <strong>9pm</strong>. Coding begins at <strong>10pm</strong>.</p>
				<p><strong>On Sunday April 10th:</strong> Coding stops at <strong>9am</strong>. We'll announce winners and have people back on buses by <strong>2pm</strong>.</p>
				<p>We'll post a more detailed schedule in late February.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="col justify vjustify gap-3">
				<h3>Packing List</h3>
				<p>CarlHacks is completely free to attend. You'll need <strong>a laptop, charger, and student ID</strong>. We'd also recommend bringing <strong>toiletries, shower shoes, a change of clothing, and a pillow</strong>. We'll provide meals, snacks, showers, and air beds for napping. If you don't have a project idea or team, don't worry! There will be team-forming events, and we find some of our best ideas come <em>during</em> the hackathon, not before. If you come with a team, note that the maximum team size is four.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="col justify vjustify gap-3">
				<h3>Join Us</h3>
				<p><strong>Registration is open until February 27th.</strong> We also accept late applications until March 14th, although they aren't eligible for travel reimbursements.</p>
				<div class="col left"><tito-button event="carlhacks/2016" class="button-light">Register Now</tito-button></div>
				<p>Shoot us an email at <a href="mailto:team@carlhacks.com">team@carlhacks.com</a> if you have any questions, disabilities, special needs, or if there's anything else we can do to ensure CarlHacks goes smoothly for you.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="fill-1 shaded-dark col">
		<img class="full-img" src="/images/rec.jpg">
		<div class="col content gap-4">
			<div class="col justify vjustify gap-3">
				<h3>Traveling to CarlHacks</h3>
				<p>CarlHacks is hosted in Northfield, Minnesota, at Carleton College's Recreation Center. If you're not already in Northfield, there are plenty of ways to get here.</p>
				<ul class="col gap-2">
					<li><p><strong>By Bus</strong> &mdash; We have buses picking up hackers from schools near the Twin Cities.</p></li>
					<li><p><strong>By Plane</strong> &mdash; We have a limited number of $150 airfare reimbursements for visitors from other states. A bus will pick you up from the airport. If you need one, be sure to apply before February 27th.</p></li>
					<li><p><strong>By Car</strong> &mdash; You're welcome to drive over! We're located at <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Recreation+Center/@44.4658458,-93.1509383,17z/data=!4m7!1m4!3m3!1s0x87f653b24725124b:0x6d95c2df8da47350!2s501+Three+Oaks+Dr,+Northfield,+MN+55057!3b1!3m1!1s0x0000000000000000:0x5b430ae20b614ef7?hl=en" class="light-link">501 Three Oaks Drive, Northfield, MN</a>.</p></li>
				</ul>
				<p>If you have any concerns or questions about travel, we're here to help! Shoot us an email at <a href="mailto:team@carlhacks.com">team@carlhacks.com</a>.</p>
			</div>
